The Prague Stock Exchange finished with fewer points at the end of the day
After the rapid fall of the morning, the Prague Stock Exchange corrected its losses.
Transactions of <0xC4><0x8C>EZ shares reached approximately half their value on a normal day.
The Prague Stock Exchange, at the beginning of trading Tuesday, reacted immediately to Monday’s drop when it fell to about 6%.
The drop this time is due to the fall in stocks on Wall Street.
Also here is the reaction of the market to the result of the vote of the American Assembly of Representatives that refused to support the stabilization plan of the secretary of the financial sector.
Falling Stocks in Asia
Shares in Asian stocks fell dramatically on Tuesday, though over the course of the day the index eventually cushioned some of the losses.
The Hong Kong Hang Seng Stock Exchange’s index throughout its financial day marked almost four percent, although it later cushioned its losses by reducing the decline by virtually 2.5 percent.
The Hang Seng China Enterprises index, which tracks Chinese stock movements on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, fell 3.8 percent, while markets in Shanghai were closed.
Sydney Stock Exchange shares lost more than five percent but, in the end, the losses dropped to 4.3 percent.
The Taiwan Stock Exchange according to the secretary of the Index fell to 3.6 percent.
“Scheduled rescue actions in the U.S. are unsafe and this influences the financial market around the world,” said Joseph Yam, head of the Hong Kong Currency Office.
Although Hong Kong is a part of China, it alone determines its monetary policy, that is, without dependence on the Central Bank of China.
Interest rates in Hong Kong are at the same level as those in the United States.
US lawmakers should reconvene as soon as possible, according to Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd, and approve a proposal to support the financial system.
Otherwise, it threatens that the falls will be felt in other countries.
Bloody Bath of American Stocks
On Monday, the American Assembly of Representatives rejected the plan to help the financial system to which 700 billion dollars should be devoted (almost 12 trillion crowns).
Legislators thus ignored President George Bush’s invitation to support his plan.
For Bush, the plan would fix the root causes of the financial crisis and help stabilize the entire economy.
On Monday, U.S. stocks went through a bloody bath and mainly the stock index picked up the biggest drop in more than 20 years.
The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell to nearly seven percent, with a similar volume drop last seen in 1987.
The index fell before it was announced but as soon as it was shown that the proposal of the assembly did not go ahead, the index began to fall freely.
Congress Withdraws: U.S. Government Can Inject $700 Billion Into Banking
The highest representatives of Congress and the government, President George W. Bush, agreed to a pact in broad terms of financial aid to the American financial system.
Their vote will take place early next week.
U.S. lawmakers sparked a rift in talks over the approval of the bailout plan in its form of aid to the U.S. financial system in the amount of $700 billion (about 12 trillion kroner).
However, it is not yet won.
Congressmen must fine-tune some details of the contract before they can make public the final form of the law and have it voted on.
The plan to help the financial system will be discussed at the House of Representatives on Monday.
Barney Frank, chairman of the Committee for Financial Services and Assembly Banking, told Reuters on Sunday.
According to some sources, the vote on the plan could be held in the Senate no earlier than Wednesday.
According to economists, the arrival of the ratification of the rescue plan should represent the announcement of a first psychologically significant factor for the revitalization of the financial market.
Then, however, there will be "disenchantment" thanks to the complex mechanisms whose aid to the market will also reach in practice.
Paulson: The plan must be effective
“We have made a great progress.
“We have resolved our differing views on how the market stabilization package should look,” Pelosi told Bloomberg.
According to her, the final vote could still take place on Sunday.
Representatives of the lawmakers met Sunday night with Finance Minister Henry Paulson to give a definitive form to the government’s fund.
It should buy unsold mortgage assets from financial corporations that lead financial firms to heavy losses and threaten the stability of the entire system.
"We are about to close the agreement on the plan, which will work and must also be effective in the market.
We still need to continue with the sanitation plan, but I think we're already at it," Paulson said.
A Sign for Asian Business
The global financial crisis has a direct impact on the rapidly falling stock market.
According to Nevada Democratic Senator Harry Reid, lawmakers are doing everything they can to get Congress to finally approve a deal on Sunday.
They want to reassure investors about the Asian financial market as these are the ones that are in the first time zone and where Congress could influence Monday’s trade.
However, for now there is nothing clear for sure about when the two chambers of the American Congress will vote and, not even, if they will not stagnate at the last moment with some problem.
Lawmakers expect it to be approved in the coming days.
The law, however, will undergo a number of changes.
The total amount intended to assist the system should be divided into two parts.
The first $350 billion must be made available as soon as possible, as requested by President George Bush.
However, Congress can block the release of the remaining amount if it has the impression that the program does not fulfill its function, which would be another 100 billion dollars and, later, the last 350 billion dollars.
Bush Appreciated the Progress of the Meetings
On the other hand, the president can veto this decision but Congress can override his veto by a majority vote.
Despite these changes, the basic idea of the program was to win financial resources for the repurchase of bad mortgage securities whose value fell because hundreds of thousands of Americans are not able to finish paying their mortgages.
“We’ve worked everything.
The House of Representatives would have to be prepared to vote on the bill on Sunday, and the Senate on Monday," said Republican Senator Judd Gregg.
President Bush is also pleased with the progress of the meetings.
Spokesman Tony Fratto said Bush was pleased with Saturday's progress and valued "both sides' efforts to stabilize our financial market and protect our economy."
Limitation of the armored contract
The chairman of the Senate Banking Committee, Christopher Dodd, chief negotiator, said lawmakers decided on the responsibility of program money for protecting taxpayers’ taxes from their losses, a easing closure of the scheduled finance plan.
The new law must also limit the so-called armored contracts for directors of the companies participating in the program, and creates a committee that will have control of the Fund.
This would have to be directed by the Ministry of Finance.
“We’ve worked very hard on it, and we’ve made a big step toward the agreement that will work and that will be effective for the market and for all Americans,” Paulson said.
The plan also aims to help homeowners who are having trouble with their payments.
The government would have to agree to new mortgage payments it buys in order to lower the monthly charges on debtors’ installment payments and make it possible for them to keep their homes.
Marek: psychological help
The proposed plan is, according to the chief economist of Patria Finance, David Marek, a good idea that will be realized but quite difficult.
"And this is why it is not known with what mechanism and at what price the problematic assets will be bought.
This will be decisive for the sharing of losses between the financial sector and the government," Marek said this week, for the iHNed.cz server.
Whether the plan is approved now or early next week is not, according to Marek, as relevant.
"Much more important is that, already this week, the congressmen agree on your support and give you their approval as soon as possible.
This important and psychological agreement to get that approval is, right now, the most important thing," Marek insisted.
